Pre-Game Insights: Former Pakistan captain Misbah-ul-Haq has slammed the national team for its fitness standards ahead of the T20 World Cup game against India.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan lost their first warm-up match against England.
The team was drubbed heavily by Jos Buttler's England, whose aggressive batting took Pakistan out of the game in just 14.4 overs.
Pakistan players suffered from fitness issues in the recently concluded Asia Cup.
The Babar Azam-led side has come into the World Cup losing their 7-match T20I series vs England.
